subSubSection.paragraph:
Head
. Head about 2.0 x wider than long, mostly black with thick pale pruinescence and covered in white hairs and scales. Eye holoptic. Frons long, 4.8 x length of ocellar tubercle, upper narrow and black; lower half triangular, 0.5 x length of upper half, with thick pale pruinescence and white scales. Ocellar tubercle slightly raised, blackish brown to black with sparse grey pruinescence, with short white hairs. Face with thick pale pruinescence and long white hairs. Gena with thick pale pruinescence and sparse white hairs. Clypeus with thick pale pruinescence and otherwise bare. Occiput with thick pale pruinescence and long white hairs. Posterior eye margin slightly concave. Antennal scape and pedicel brown with thick pale pruinescence, scape with long black hairs on dorsal half, and white hairs on ventral half, pedicel with short black hairs; flagellum black without pruinescence, bare. Scape 2.2 x as long as wide, and 2.7 x as long as pedicel, uniform from base to apex. Pedicel as long as wide. Flagellum 12.0 x as long as wide, 2.8 x as long as scape + pedicel, 3.4 x as long as scape, conical and slightly laterally compressed, one-segmented with apical stylus (
Fig. 2c
). Palpus not extending beyond oral cavity, black with short white hairs, one-segmented, without palpal pit. Mouthparts slender, 3.7 x as long as eye length, 2.2 x as long as head length, labellum large and fleshy (
Fig. 2h
).

Female. Body length 9.1–12.5 mm , wing length 9.3–13.0 mm. Very similar to male, except frons black with thick pale pruinescence, 2.6 x as wide as ocellar tubercle, frons with short white scales admixed with brownish yellow setae ( Fig. 2l ). Ocellar tubercle covered with admixed long black hairs and short white hairs. Occiput covered in white hairs admixed with brownish yellow setae. Nine acanthophorite spines present on each side of tergite 9+10 (
Fig. 3g
).
